      <h2>The&nbsp;dangers of unbooked minicabs</h2>

<p>While London is safe for most people travelling at night, we still have major concerns over the dangers of travelling in unbooked minicabs.</p>

<p><a href="/campaign/safer-travel">Find out more about how to make sure your minicab is booked</a>.</p>

<h2>What we're doing</h2>

<p>We work closely with the Taxi and Private Hire trade, the MPS and the City of London Police to ensure the safety of passengers using London's taxi and private hire services.</p>

<p>We directly fund 68 dedicated police cab enforcement officers, and are increasing the number of TfL TPH compliance officers.<br />
<br />
These officers conduct targeted plain clothes and high visibility operations to detect, disrupt and deter illegal and non-compliant TPH activity.</p>

<h2>Reporting touting and illegal cab activity</h2>

<p>Licensed and law-abiding taxi and private hire drivers and other members of the public often have valuable information on touting and other cab-related offences across London.</p>

<p><a href="/help-and-contact/reporting-touting-and-illegal-cabs">Let us know if you have information about touting or illegal cab activity</a>.</p>

<h3>Taxi driver identifiers</h3>

<p>All taxi drivers are required to display driver identifiers when plying for hire as a condition of licence.</p>

<p>If you witness a driver not displaying their identifiers, displaying the wrong identifiers or you suspect displaying fake identifiers, or who may be plying for hire outside of their licence area, you can&nbsp;report this to us.</p>
      
           
      
      
        
          
